cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.MM 

This paper explores the properties of a convolutional encoder-decoder network used as a prior for natural images, specifically in the context of denoising. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper analyzes the optimization trajectories of the network, which suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the frequency components of the image and early stopping, which could relate to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM).
